verbose_text: Acetylcholine, combined with alpha7 nicotinic acetylcholine receptors (a7-nAChR), which are located between macrophages, monocytes, lymphocytes and dendritic cell surfaces, block the NF kappa B signaling pathway, inhibiting pro inflammatory cytokine synthesis and alleviating the inflammatory response.
